The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma, Showbiz Correspondent TODAY is a special day to dancer cum singer Sweet Mobby, a prison officer by profession as she turns 28. Born Moreblessing Khumalo, Sweet Mobby continues to follow her dream of penetrating the local entertainment scene while plying the prison officer trade as she is employed by the Zimbabwe Prisons and Correctional Services (ZPCS). Through her career Sweet Mobby has once worked with South Africa-based artiste Diliza on his Amapiano single Ongenamali track where she did the vocals. <img class="wp-image-546132 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Sweet-Mobby-34.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Sweet-Mobby-34.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/05/Sweet-Mobby-34-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Sweet Mobby A talented dancer, she featured on Sandra Ndebeleâ€™s 2017 Tshibilika music video. She has also worked with talented musicians Mzoe 7, Leticia Ontle, Sugar Shayne, Leeknotic Mambo and DJ Cooperman and has shared the stage with Jah Signal in South Africa. From the Chronicle Showbiz Team, we say Happy 28th birthday mntase. @mthabisi_mthire